        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>May 19, 1854</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phi<hi rend="sup">la</hi></placeName> Dear Sir</p>
            <p>Not aware of the Value of your last<lb/> shipment &amp; with out this knowledge
                of<lb/> the actual Contents I have not insured<lb/> In <sic>refering</sic> to your
                advice of the <date>10th</date> I <sic>omited</sic><lb/> to say I beg to decline
                sending any Bibles<lb/> to <placeName>Texas</placeName> as the chances are you would
                never<lb/> hear from them again, If I could pack them<lb/> with
                    <persName>Harmans</persName> goods at any time I should<lb/> feel sure of then
                safely but not otherwise. I<lb/> wait <persName>Mr Osterman's</persName>
                <sic>adviseing</sic> me He will<lb/> receive the 2 Bibles are I send them &amp;
                hope<lb/> you have written to Him, If opportunity<lb/> offers will send <persName>Dr
                    Mayer</persName> Book to <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> I doubt if I
                receive one Cent from the<lb/> Congregation until after the arrival of those<lb/>
                other Books, I fear I shall be compel'd<lb/> 'ere another Year to again take the
                responsible<lb/> office of Parnass or I fear the worst result<lb/> to our
                Institution &amp; the standing of its Credit<lb/> I would prefer to never again
                resume office but a national<lb/> feeling will urge me on Its hard after so
                many<lb/> Years of hard Labour to make our People &amp; their</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>Institutions respected that others shall gain<lb/> the ascendancy &amp; be unable to
                keep up<lb/> its respectability. I hope ere long to<lb/> give you a better account
                of your subscribers<lb/> here but they are hard to get money from<lb/>
                <persName>G. G. Levi</persName> I wrote a note to but <sic>He</sic><lb/> never
                called or <add>?</add> me. He is<lb/> going to reside in <placeName>Chicago
                    Ill.</placeName><lb/> I told you a <hi rend="underline">secret</hi> when the
                    <sic>Body</sic> of <persName>Mr<lb/> Touro</persName> would leave here &amp; 2
                    <sic>Days</sic><lb/> after rec'd your <date>May</date> Number &amp;
                perceived<lb/> It was public what was told me as<lb/> a profound Secret.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Credit <persName>J P Hayes</persName> 3..00<lb/>
                <persName>Red J R Gutheim</persName> 3..00<lb/>
                <persName>L Goldsmith</persName> 3..00</p>
            <p>neither of these <sic>Have</sic> I recd the money from but<lb/> will do so next week
                &amp; I would like them<lb/> to be Credited in the <date>June</date> Number<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Goldsmith</persName> will at same time take his<lb/> Bible,
                    <persName>J. C. Labatt</persName>
                <sic>dont</sic> come<lb/> near me I shall again call<lb/> on him</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">May God Bless you &amp; grant<lb/> you many Years of Happiness is
                the<lb/> constant wish of your friend</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName>
            </p>
            <p
                rend="The following is written sideways in the left hand margin, near the center of the page."
                >I enclose Duplicate<lb/> of Yesterday</p>
        </body>
